<font color="#FF0000">WHO'S WHO.</font><br>
<tt>Sat Oct 18  0:00:24 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
<br>
Who's Who.<br><br>
My name is Paul Mahar.  I have achieved 15 minutes of fame regarding my service in Vietnam.<br><br>
I was featured on Now with Tom Brokaw in August of 1994 and People Magazine on March 21 of that same year.<br><br>
I was a Wolfhound in Cu Chi in from Nov.  66 to Dec  67.  I spent my entire tour in Vietnam in the place of another man.  I never went through basic or AIT training.  Truth is always stranger than fiction.<br><br>
I was a combat veteran with, perhaps, some different viewpoints about the war and it's aftermath.  Those of us baby boomers know that it was a hell of a time to be alive, just like any other time, I guess.<br><br>
I entered a thought or two in the tunnel rat category and will add some thoughts from time to time.  My best to all who read this web page.
<p><code>-- pgmahar@nidlink.com  (Paul Mahar) </code><p>


